 \Delta\vec y(x) = (\Delta y_1(x), \Delta y_2(x), \cdots, \Delta y_n(x)) 
\hat n
 \hat n = \frac{\Delta\vec y}{\lVert\Delta\vec y \lVert} \;\therefore\; \Delta\vec y = \hat n\cdot\lVert\Delta\vec y\lVert = \hat n\cdot\Delta\bar y 
 d\vec y = \hat n\cdot\lVert d\vec y\lVert = \hat n\cdot d\bar y 
 \frac{d\vec y}{dx} = \hat n\cdot\frac{d\bar y}{dx} 
\hat n
